number=[1,2,3,4,5,6]

for num in number:
    if num % 2 ==0:
        print(f"{num}is even")



for loops are best for iterating over sequences.
while loops are used when the number of iterations is not predetermined.
Loops can be nested, meaning one loop inside another.
